23/08/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in Gjirokastra seized 60kg of marijuana on Sunday (August 22nd) in a car near the village of Nepravishta and are searching for two suspects. 
One of them is allegedly from the village of Lazarat, the marijuana cultivation capital of southern Albania.
Also on Sunday, Gjirokastra police destroyed 600 marijuana plants in the fields outside Lazarat. 
Police arrested the alleged owner of the field and are searching for two more people. 
The operation, dubbed Sunrise, is the first in the village, where even police authorities could not enter for years. 
(Ora News, Klan, Alsat, Balkan Web, Lajmifundit, Telegrafi - 22/08/10)
